{
  "texts": [
    "In what follows, we refer to Event tokens as dynamic features and RGB tokens as static features.",
    "Dynamic feature matrices D f ∈ R T ×B×D and static feature matrices S f ∈ R B×S are provided, where T represents the number of time steps, B the batch size, and D and S the feature dimensions.",
    "Consequently, D and S also denote the number of dynamic nodes and static feature nodes, respectively.",
    "An overview of our proposed HyperGraph-guided completion framework for effective frame and event stream aggregation, termed EvRainDrop.",
    "Specifically, we first partition and map the given RGB and event stream inputs, and then process them through a visual encoder to obtain RGB and Event tokens."
  ]
}